81typedef struct {

150typedef struct {
151 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *stats;
152 int num_frames;
153} FIRST_PASS_INFO;
154
155static INLINE void fps_init_first_pass_info(FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info,
156 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *stats,
157 int num_frames) {
158 first_pass_info->stats = stats;
159 first_pass_info->num_frames = num_frames;
160}
161
162static INLINE int fps_get_num_frames(const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info) {
163 return first_pass_info->num_frames;
164}
165
166static INLINE const FIRSTPASS_STATS *fps_get_frame_stats(
167 const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info, int show_idx) {
168 if (show_idx < 0 || show_idx >= first_pass_info->num_frames) {
169 return NULL;
170 }
171 return &first_pass_info->stats[show_idx];
172}

254#if CONFIG_RATE_CTRL
255/* Call this function to get info about the next group of pictures.
256 * This function should be called after vp9_create_compressor() when encoding
257 * starts or after vp9_get_compressed_data() when the encoding process of
258 * the last group of pictures is just finished.
259 */
260void vp9_get_next_group_of_picture(const struct VP9_COMP *cpi,
261 int *first_is_key_frame, int *use_alt_ref,
262 int *coding_frame_count, int *first_show_idx,
263 int *last_gop_use_alt_ref);
264
265/*!\brief Call this function before coding a new group of pictures to get
266 * information about it.
267 * \param[in] oxcf Encoder config
268 * \param[in] frame_info Frame info
269 * \param[in] first_pass_info First pass stats
270 * \param[in] rc Rate control state
271 * \param[in] show_idx Show index of the first frame in the group
272 * \param[in] multi_layer_arf Is multi-layer alternate reference used
273 * \param[in] allow_alt_ref Is alternate reference allowed
274 * \param[in] first_is_key_frame Is the first frame in the group a key frame
275 * \param[in] last_gop_use_alt_ref Does the last group use alternate reference
276 *
277 * \param[out] use_alt_ref Does this group use alternate reference
278 *
279 * \return Returns coding frame count
280 */
281int vp9_get_gop_coding_frame_count(const struct VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf,
282 const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
283 const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info,
284 const RATE_CONTROL *rc, int show_idx,
285 int multi_layer_arf, int allow_alt_ref,
286 int first_is_key_frame,
287 int last_gop_use_alt_ref, int *use_alt_ref);
288
289int vp9_get_coding_frame_num(const struct VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf,
290 const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
291 const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info,
292 int multi_layer_arf, int allow_alt_ref);
293
294/*!\brief Compute a key frame binary map indicates whether key frames appear
295 * in the corresponding positions. The passed in key_frame_map must point to an
296 * integer array with length equal to first_pass_info->num_frames, which is the
297 * number of show frames in the video.
298 */
299void vp9_get_key_frame_map(const struct VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf,
300 const FRAME_INFO *frame_info,
301 const FIRST_PASS_INFO *first_pass_info,
302 int *key_frame_map);
